# Financial Risk Management Capital Balancing Item Liability Component Adjusted Amount

## identifier
de5136

## status
Standard

## type
undefined

## definition
Report the adjusted value of the liability component less the value of effective borrowings and tax liabilities.

The Liability Component is determined as the realistic value of liabilities of the General Fund plus, in the case of a friendly society, the reserve in respect of servicing expenses and investment-linked business.

The adjustment is for the prescribed yield change in the discount rate used in their valuation, in accordance with the solvency standard.

